cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the analysis of fluorescence or histopathological images of cells. It may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as the method involves ranking cuts according to a scoring metric. The use of geometric partitioning suggests that it may also belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category, but since the focus is on image analysis, this is less likely. Finally, the use of a set of 2420 clumps of nuclei suggests that it may also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category, and the use of cuts to partition the nuclei suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
